arts.ttl: AFC Wimbledon boss on Cheltenham defeat after missing out on chance to move into automatic spots
arts.sum: Wimbledon brought the game level in the 36th minute when James Tilley headed Josh Neufville’s cross back towards Joe Day’s goal and the ball bounced beyond Robins keeper Joe Day. Browne then flashed a cross along the face of the goal in the 72nd minute, which took a deflection but was unable to find a way into Day’s net.

arts.ttl: AFC Wimbledon v Cheltenham Town RECAP: Matty Taylor seals away success
arts.sum: Cheltenham Town: Day; Bakare, Stubbs, Bradbury; Power (Adedokun 45+1), Kinsella, Dieng, Archer, Thomas (Williams 66); Miller (Taylor 66), Hay. Subs not used: Diallo, Dulson, King, Backwell. Cheltenham Town claimed their fourth away win of the season by upsetting promotion-chasing AFC Wimbledon at Plough Lane on Tuesday night.

arts.ttl: Matty Taylor winner earns Cheltenham victory over promotion-chasing Wimbledon
arts.sum: Ashley Hay had put Cheltenham in front, only for James Tilley to equalise.

arts.ttl: Massively let down by officials, disrespect from Colchester United boss Danny Cowley and injury blow - Cheltenham Town manager Michael Flynn after home defeat
arts.sum: The amount of games they were playing today was typical of Danny Cowley's teams. Lots to improve on, but I was proud of the way our players stood up for each other today and battled and kept going, even though we haven't won the game.

Wimbledon's 2-0 win over Notts County at the weekend ended four games without a win. Cheltenham's 1-0 defeat to Colchester on Saturday made it four games without a win and their slim play-off chances...

arts.ttl: Johnnie Jackson delighted AFC Wimbledon squad shared goalscoring burden in Notts County win
arts.sum: “I am very pleased with Joe Lewis’ goal,” said Jackson. Defender Joe Lewis opened the scoring when he guided his header in off the far post from a corner just after the half-hour mark, before midfielder Alistair Smith fired home from the edge of the box 15 minutes later to double their lead.

arts.ttl: Preview: AFC Wimbledon vs. Cheltenham Town - prediction, team news, lineups
arts.sum: Sports Mole previews Tuesday's League Two clash between AFC Wimbledon and Cheltenham Town, including predictions, team news and possible lineups.
